</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1442,1504]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
The specific epithet is the Latin adjective ‘ 
<emphasis box="[696,848,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">chrysopterus</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[873,888,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">a</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[913,949,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">um</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘golden-winged’, referring to the entirely yellow corium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
